        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 6</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="1">And this is the commandment, the statutes, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            judgments which the Lord your God commanded to teach you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            to do them in the land to which you are crossing to inherit it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="2">That you may fear the Lord your God,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            to keep all his statutes and his commandments which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            I am commanding you: you and your son and your son’s son,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            all the days of your life, and that your days may be prolonged.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="3">And you shall listen, oh Israel, and you shall be watchful
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            to do it, that it may be good for you and that you may multiply
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            very much, as the Lord God of your fathers has spoken to you:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            a land flowing |with| milk and honey.</l>
                        <l n="4"><emph>Listen, Israel:</emph>
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            <emph>YHWH is our God. YHWH is one.</emph> Accept, oh Israel:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            The Lord our God, the LORD is one.</l>
                        <l n="5">And you shall love
                            <milestone unit="page" n="291v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            with all your might.</l>
                        <l n="6">And the words,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            those which I command you this day, shall be in your mind.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="7">And you shall teach them to your children, and you shall talk of them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            when you sit in your house and when you walk by the way and before you lie
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            down and after you rise.</l>
                        <l n="8">And,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            as if they were bound, keep them for a sign on your hand,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            and they shall be as if a memorial engraved
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            between your eyes.</l>
                        <l n="9">And keep them on
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            the doorposts of your house and on your gates, as if they were written |there|,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            <seg type="commented" n="#seg001" />so that the commandments of the Law
                            may be in your mind every time you come in and go out<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn1"
                                type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="10">And it shall be, when the Lord your God brings you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            to the land which he swore to your fathers, to Abraham,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give you great and good cities
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            that you did not build,</l>
                        <l n="11">And houses full of everything
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            good that you did not fill, and wells dug that you did not dig,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            vineyards and olive trees that you did not plant, and if you eat and
                            satiate yourself,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="12">Take heed to yourself, lest you forget the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            service of Lord who brought you out from the land of Egypt,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            from the reign of slaves.</l>
                        <l n="13">You shall fear the Lord your God and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            serve him, and you shall swear to the truth by his name.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="292r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="14">You shall not walk after the service of other gods,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            of the gods of the people who are around you,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="15">Because the Lord your God is a jealous God among you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            lest the anger of the Lord your God be kindled against you, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            he destroy you from off the face of the earth.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="16">You shall not test the Lord your God as you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            tested him in Massah.</l>
                        <l n="17">You shall keep the commandments
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            of the Lord your God and his laws and his statutes
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            which he has commanded you.</l>
                        <l n="18">And you shall do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            what seems right and good in the sight of the Lord, that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            it may be well with you, and that you may come and inherit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            the good land which the Lord swore to your fathers,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="19">To push all your enemies from before you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            as the Lord has spoken.</l>
                        <l n="20">And if your son ever asks you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            saying, “What are the laws and the statutes,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and the judgments which the Lord our God has commanded you?”,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="21">Then you shall say to your son, “We were slaves to Pharaoh
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            in the land of Egypt, and the Lord brought us out from Egypt
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            with a strong hand.</l>
                        <l n="22">And the Lord gave us signs
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            and wonders, great and bad, in Egypt at Pharaoh
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            and at all his household in our sight.</l>
                        <l n="23">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="292v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            And he brought us out from there in order to bring us, to give us
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            the land which he swore to our fathers.</l>
                        <l n="24">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            And the Lord commanded us to do all these
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            statutes, to fear the Lord our God for our good
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            every day, to keep us alive, like today.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="25">And it shall be a merit for us: if we observe to do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            all these commandments before the Lord our God,
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-8-1" n="8" next="ADub.III.73.005.007.trl.xml#line-8-2" />
                            as he has commanded us.”</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
